The paper explores the intellectual and social similarity among scholarly journals by analyzing the networks of editors, authors, and co-citations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social Network Analysis (cs.SNA), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). These sub-categories are all relevant to the paper's focus on analyzing networks and communities within scholarly journals.
